5 Section 7. Section 2-15-2044, MCA, is amended to read:
6 "2-15-2044. Montana end of watch trust board. (1) There is a volunteer board to oversee the
7 administration of the Montana end of watch trust provided for in 2-15-2041 and to determine the eligibility of
8 applicants seeking funds from the trust. The board is attached to the department for administrative purposes
9 only, as provided in 2-15-121.
10 (2) The board consists of five members appointed by the attorney general, including:
11 (a) a representative of the Montana sheriffs and peace officers association;
12 (b) a representative of the Montana police protective association;
13 (c) a representative of the association of Montana troopers;
14 (d) a representative of the Montana association of chiefs of police; and
15 (e) a representative from the department.
16 (3) The board shall:
17 (a) meet at least once each fiscal year; and
18 (b) act as an advocate for law enforcement officers catastrophically injured in the line of duty and
19 the surviving immediate family members of officers who died in the line of duty; and convene as necessary to
20 review applications and determine the eligibility of applicants. ; AND
21 (c) settle disputes and concerns regarding trust benefits.;
22 (C) REVIEW THE BOARD OF INVESTMENTS ANNUAL REPORT FOR THE FUND.
23 (4) The representatives in subsection (2) must be sworn actors of a participating agency."
